n tests for cache auto-configuration use ApplicationContextRunner; this is the practical in-process way to exercise CacheAutoConfiguration without starting a full application or external cache service.\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"agent_guidance\": \"No environment variables or system properties are required. Prefer in-process tests around CacheProperties, CacheManagerCustomizers, CacheMetricsRegistrar where applicable, and CacheAutoConfiguration with an @EnableCaching user configuration. The simple/concurrent-map/no-op/generic cache paths can be covered without Redis, Couchbase, Hazelcast, Infinispan, JCache, Caffeine, or Cache2k services.\",\n      \"risks\": [\n        \"Provider-specific paths are guarded by optional classpath conditions; tests that directly target Redis, Couchbase, Hazelcast, Infinispan, JCache, Caffeine, Cache2k, or actuator endpoint integrations may need additional provider dependencies and should not be attempted unless deliberately added.\",\n        \"No Docker image is needed for meaningful baseline cache auto-configuration coverage; external cache services would only be needed for integration-style provider tests.\"\n      ],\n      \"applied_setup\": [\n        {\n          \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n          \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-autoconfigure:4.1.0\",\n          \"result\": \"applied\",\n          \"target\": \"tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-cache/4.1.0/build.gradle\"\n        },\n        {\n          \"kind\": \"dependency\",\n          \"coordinate\": \"org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-test:4.1.0\",\n          \"result\": \"applied\",\n          \"target\": \"tests/src/org.springframework.boot/spring-boot-cache/4.1.0/build.gradle\"\n        }\n      ],\n      \"input_evidence\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"issue\",\n          \"summary\": \"#8412 Support for org.springframework.boot:spring-boot-cache:4.1.0; label=library-new-request; body_chars=39\"\n        },\n      